<br>
You're in the extreme minority when you say &quot;it was boring&quot;.  The music wasn't &quot;bad&quot;, it was simply from a different era.  Same with the acting.  If you don't appreciate filmmaking from different eras (and different styles), that's your right.  But don't assume that the majority of people who have seen the movie will agree with you.<br>
<br>
*And also, you say that they're copycats because they use similar camera angles? Does that mean that all movies that use sound are copycatting the first movie to do that?*<br>
<br>
Those aren't even comparable.  You're trying to compare a technological improvement to a style of filmmaking.  Of course everyone was going to start making &quot;talkies&quot; when the technology was created.  It was a revolution in film that improved and expanded what directors could do with the medium.<br>
<br>
Wells didn't create any new technology when he decided what lighting to use and what camera angles to use it with.  It was his style and it worked very well, so many filmmakers that followed mimicked his style. <p>The surest sign of intelligent life in the universe is that none of it has tried contacting us.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thebraneatingzombie>The Bran Eating Zombie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/9/02 11:04:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11559.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.marilynmanson.com/manson/images/portrait/portrait030.jpg length=180 width=120></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: gay movie makers</span><hr size=1> It's not hard to be creative when there are like ten other movies out there. Sure he was creative, and it was a great movie for it's time, it's just not that impressive a movie anymore, and it bothers me when people talk about it being the best movie ever, just because it was a great movie when it came out. I am hugely more impressed when people come out with original techniques and such these days. <p>Alone and Empty.<br>
