HUH?  Citizen Kane came out in 1941.  Each  major studio was pumping out about ONE PICTURE PER WEEK.  Do you know how many pictures the major studios pump out per YEAR nowadays?  About 15.  You need to do a little more research before saying there were about &quot;10 movies out there&quot;.  Citizen Kane came out AFTER people like Mary Pickford, Humphrey Bogart, Ingrid Bergman, Charlie Chaplin, and Buster Keaton had been on the scene for years.  That's some impressive competition.<br>
